radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation with no evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. The pancreas shows normal attenuation without focal lesions. The spleen is normal. Both adrenal glands are normal. Kidneys are normal in size with no focal lesions or hydronephrosis. Distal appendix is dilated up to 1.3 cm with a 0.7 cm appendicolith, wall edema, and periappendiceal fat stranding. No extraluminal air or drainable fluid collection. The stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs are unremarkable. No lymphadenopathy or vascular abnormalities noted. No evidence of osseous lesions or acute fractures.
